<TITLE> WB okays two projects for Sidr survivors </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, July 2 (bdnews24.com) - The World Bank has approved two new projects for poor families affected by cyclone Sidr, slum children and people with disabilities, the WB said in a statement Tuesday. The bank granted an additional financing of $50 million for the social investment programme project meant to help restore assets, and livelihoods for families affected by cyclone Sidr, the statement said. Another $35 million project named disability and children-at-risk project has been designed to expand the coverage, use, and quality of social care services for these vulnerable groups. "This is one of the operations in a series of the World Bank's planned support to respond to Bangladesh's request for rehabilitation and reconstruction assistance in the aftermath of the cyclone," said World Bank country director Xian Zhu. "A quick disbursing budget support has already been approved and a longer-term support for disaster management an emergency recovery credit is currently under preparation." bd
